text: Antti Ilari Törmänen (born September 19, 1970) is a retired professional ice hockey player and current head coach of EHC Biel in Switzerland's National League. He played for the Ottawa Senators, Jokerit, HV71 and Södertälje SK over 14 seasons. On 15 March 2020, Törmänen tested positive for COVID-19. ==References== Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:Finnish ice hockey left wingers Category:Ice hockey coaches Category:People from Espoo
